38TH MIDWEST SYMPOSIUM ON CIRCUITS AND SYSTEMS  / // _/ /   //  /\  \
Hotel Gloria, Rio de Janeiro, Brazil           /  _  \ /   / \  \/  /
August 13-16, 1995                             \_/ \_/ \__/   \____/ 

The 1995 Midwest Symposium on Circuits and Systems will be organized 
by the Federal University of Rio de Janeiro and co-sponsored by the 
IEEE Circuits and Systems Society. The Symposium will be devoted to all
aspects of the theory, design and applications of circuits and systems.

Topics include, but are not limited to:

Analog and Digital Circuit Design    Analog and Digital VLSI Design
Solid State Circuits                 Microwave circuits
Computer Aided Design                Fault Analysis
Analog/Digital Signal Processing     Image Processing
Analog/Digital Filters               Adaptive Signal Processing
Neural Networks                      Expert and Intelligent Systems
Computer Networks and Circuits       Petri Networks
Control Systems                      Robotics
Nonlinear Circuits and Systems       Large Scale Systems
Fuzzy Systems                        Power Electronics
Power Systems                        Biomedical Systems

The main activities of the Symposium will be:

Technical Paper Sections             Special Sections and Tutorials
Plenary Sections                     Pre-symposium courses
Companions' activities

